<paragraph id="0C0736939F44FF854CF4596F799BFAFB" blockId="1.[151,1436,1285,2031]" box="[198,469,1325,1351]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Host plants. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C0736939F44FF854CF459177B9AFA5B" blockId="1.[151,1436,1285,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Description. Total body length 
<quantity id="CB409B769F44FF854E0A59177ADBFAD3" box="[568,661,1365,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="CB409B769F44FF854EDF59177B02FAD3" box="[749,844,1365,1391]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
. Each elytron with three black patches at humeral callus, below scutellum and at apex (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F44FF854E6B593F7A87FA2B" box="[601,713,1405,1431]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs 1, 5</figureCitation>
). Pronotum blackish except for anterior and lateral margins being light brown. Head with vertex dark brown and facial part light brown. Six basal antennomeres light brown, rest black. Legs dark brown, except for tibial apex light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C0736939F44FF854CF559B7797CF943" blockId="1.[151,1436,1285,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
In lateral view, vertex and frons form convex line, their intersection being concave and proximal end of frons higher than vertex. Vertex punctate (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F44FF854EB85A5F7A9DF98B" box="[650,723,1565,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Antennal callus slightly raised, oblique, shorter than wide, low near supracallinal sulcus, high near supraantennal sulcus, separated from each other by midfrontal depression. Suprafrontal sulcus well developed, midfrontal sulcus poorly developed. Frontal ridge slightly wrinkled. Anterofrontal ridge without vertical carina medially. Maxillary palpus with preapical palpomere subequal to half of apical palpomere. Third antennomere nearly as long as second (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F44FF854FD45AFF7C61F96B" box="[998,1071,1725,1751]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Tenth antennomere nearly as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C0736939F44FF864CF55B4F7CC8FEBE" blockId="1.[151,1436,1285,2031]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,152,338]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Lateral margin of pronotum nearly straight (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F44FF854EE65B4F7B52F89B" box="[724,796,1805,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), anterolateral callosity forms obtuse denticle at pore. Disc shiny, punctation fine, stronger than that on vertex. Antebasal transverse impression absent except for imperceptible curved longitudinal line laterally on each side near posterior margin. Scutellum shiny, impunctate, triangular, wider than long, apex narrowly rounded. Elytron with well developed humeral callus (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F44FF8549785BC778E9F87B" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs 1, 5</figureCitation>
), with very slight depression posteriorly, maximum width at proximal 1/3. Striae slightly depressed. Interstices flat with extremely minute punctures. Width of interstices subequal to 4 
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F44FF8548115B977C7CF853" bold="true" box="[1059,1074,2005,2031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">–</emphasis>
7 times diameter of a puncture. Epipleuron oblique, not reaching apex. Metasternum about two times as long as prosternum. Metafemur with flat ridge along its posterior edge (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F47FF864E005C827A32FF66" box="[562,636,192,218]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Metatibia straight in lateral view, curved from dorsal view, proximal 1/3 dorsally convex, rest of surface nearly flat. Claw longer than metatibial spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0C0736939F47FF864CF55D527B6DFEEE" blockId="2.[151,1436,152,338]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Median lobe of aedeagus slightly constricted in middle (
<figureCitation id="94832A169F47FF864F6B5D527BEEFE96" box="[857,928,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-123@2.[156,1436,397,1937]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Phaelota assamensis. 1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views." pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), widening apically, with obtuse denticle at apex. Apical one third slightly flattened on ventral side.
</paragraph>
<caption id="58C7661B9F47FF864CA55BEC7B6DF854" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" startId="2.[151,269,1966,1990]" targetBox="[157,1428,398,1923]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="0C0736939F47FF864CA55BEC7B6DF854" blockId="2.[151,1435,1966,2024]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F47FF864CA55BEC790CF87A" bold="true" box="[151,322,1966,1990]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="3ECCEA819F47FF864D785BEC7A7EF879" box="[330,560,1966,1989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName id="CBB84D109F47FF864D785BEC7A62F879" box="[330,556,1966,1989]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Phaelota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assamensis">Phaelota assamensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
1 – dorsal habitus, 2 – head, 3 – pronotum, 4 – metafemur, 5 – lateral habitus, 6 – median lobe of aedeagus in ventral, lateral, and dorsal views.
</paragraph>
</caption>
